  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Ezra 6:8-9",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezra 6:8-9",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "That of the king’s goods, forthwith expenses be given — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That the work might not be stopped for want of money to carry it on, he orders certain sums to be paid them out of his own revenue. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And that which they have need of both young bullocks, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — He orders that they should be supplied with every thing they wanted for maintaining the sacrifices at the temple, when it should be built, both for burnt-offerings and meat- offerings. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Let it be given them day by day — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That the morning and evening sacrifices might not fail to be offered every day.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
